    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "ok i think i follow the shear flow part. but i was thinking about the actual space between the bars. since the concrete is poured around them, the rebar is basically hidden deep inside this solid mass. does anything ever happen to the bond over time? like is there any risk of something \"getting into\" those small gaps between the steel and the concrete that might mess up the distribution?",
